To the 4th hee saith, hee knoweth nothing thereof./
To the 5th hee saith, the said shipp ''fortune'' was seized and taken by the said English friggat about a league from the English shoare, shee being not then under the Command of English fort or Castle, nor within shott of any Englishman of warr lying in or neere the downes for the defense and service of this Commonwealth./
To the 6th hee saith, That the said two french men of warr never deserted the pursuite of the said shipp ''ffortune'', till shee was by the English frigatts Companie seized as aforesaid, which was about a league from the English coast according to this deponents judgement, but not within the Command of any such fort Castle or shipp as is interrate./
