And further deposeth not.
To the xixth. Article he saith that all and singular the dammages which befell the sayd goods were caused by the fury and violence of the foresayd stormes and tempests; and by the disaster upon the forementioned sands and not by or through the neglect wilfulnes or default whatsoever of the sayd Martin Barnhide or his shippes Company, which this deponent being Carpenter of the sayd shipp and sayling in her as aforesayd well knoweth to be true, And otherwise he cannot depose.
